(* Beginning of Notebook Content *)
Notebook[{
Cell["Quantum Systems Engineering, by Computing", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"c89324f7-5f52-41d1-bcf9-4210bb70494c"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["A computation-first tour of quantum systems \
engineering in the Wolfram QuantumFramework.", "TI"]], "Text",ExpressionUUID->\
"d3b84520-96ae-4ffe-b671-b5e5a7bd6ffd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This document walks the entire arc of quantum systems engineering, from \
Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger's equation to quantum sensing, and teaches every idea \
by ",
 StyleBox["building it as a computation you can run, modify, and break",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". The conviction is Feynman-flavored: if we cannot compute it, we have not \
really understood it. So every claim below is immediately followed by a cell \
that demonstrates or verifies it, and every number you see was produced by \
running the code, not asserted from a formula sheet."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ef8db518-67de-4172-870a-32090b65a8eb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We start with a particle trapped in a box, and use it to motivate the jump \
from messy calculus to clean linear algebra. We then build the engineer's two \
workhorses, the ",
 StyleBox["qubit",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " and the ",
 StyleBox["quantum harmonic oscillator",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", drive them with fields, and watch them flop. We scale up to many qubits, \
gates, and circuits; send a state across a channel by teleportation; open the \
system to its environment and watch coherence decay; and finally turn that \
same fragility into a precision ",
 StyleBox["sensor",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". A closing section works four of these threads into extended, \
self-contained examples."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"aa7912e1-c688-4521-a96e-4d846535f273"],

Cell["\<\
A practical note on how to read this. Evaluate the cells top to bottom, as if \
this were one long laboratory session. Each section is self-contained enough \
to start from, but variables defined earlier are reused. Change the numbers. \
Detune the drive, raise the noise, add a qubit. The framework will tell you \
what happens.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4c861218-6025-4373-83a4-ac1ef2ae7f86"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9dbb7973-0381-44e8-b93e-7423fe256908"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Everything below uses one paclet plus its second-quantization sub-package. \
Load both up front. The sub-package carries the oscillator and quantum-optics \
tools (",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "AnnihilationOperator"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "16391ffa-701c-4e6d-b9df-e8245e5078ad"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "FockState"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "be052b87-1bf4-41cc-ba45-5bcd123b3416"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "CoherentState"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "e53cfedd-0782-4b33-bee7-e95cdff73b88"],
 ", the quadrature operators, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "OperatorVariance"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "ccd58500-78e3-40e4-8e05-3a8a0e9e1335"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "G2Coherence"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "bcf3d309-1ce4-47bc-97e4-4aabd2198d63"],
 "); a bare ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Needs"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "59b75cfb-2472-4f6e-b3d3-1a30209605cb"],
 " of the main context leaves these inert, so we load it now even though it \
is first needed in Part 5."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"aae1fd6b-4a6e-46f0-958d-de0ab031d72c"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`\>\"", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`SecondQuantization`\>\"",
   "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"711ad373-48d4-4be9-b52d-7f4beae36eb2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The three central objects are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumState"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a22ac8b2-f034-4aa8-b88d-ac85b69030ef"],
 " (a ket or a density matrix), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumOperator"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "39af2459-5d3a-4c98-9ad7-9a0d00d9c983"],
 " (a matrix that acts on states, including Hamiltonians and gates), and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumCircuitOperator"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "84650b6c-fee9-48ec-bf88-3d65273cc8bf"],
 " (an ordered list of operations). Each is a ",
 StyleBox["property-carrying object", "TI"],
 ": you ask it questions with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"object", "[", "\"\<Property\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"4a546d36-c707-4a67-be82-8d79bdd45ee1"],
 " rather than calling dozens of separate functions. That is the single most \
important habit to build here. When you want the Bloch vector, the purity, \
whether an operator is Hermitian, or a variance, ask the object: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"qs", "[", "\"\<BlochVector\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"5bdc2c58-58c0-4198-88f3-ac0b58c2c8d4"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"qs", "[", "\"\<Purity\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "bb3c654b-e740-48d4-8067-e5f60134b24d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"op", "[", "\"\<HermitianQ\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"21197c9d-ea88-442a-ba13-848389a3f03b"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"OperatorVariance", "[", 
   RowBox[{"qs", ",", " ", "op"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "3e834c99-8db9-44d3-a9e8-dedd6513adb6"],
 ". We reach for raw matrices only to ",
 StyleBox["build", "TI"],
 " an operator, never to interrogate one. We will lean on that pattern \
constantly."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3d1dc9de-37c8-469e-85a9-3e489a1fce37"],

Cell["Part 1: From wave mechanics to a finite Hilbert space", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"a9624dab-3500-41ef-ac9e-d5e4faab83b4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We open with Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger's equation and the infinite square \
well because it is the simplest place where energy quantization falls out of \
a boundary condition. A particle of mass ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["m", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3d034ebf-6b5f-4370-849a-c2effc02ff99"],
 " confined to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"0", "\[LessEqual]", 
   StyleBox["x", "TI"], "\[LessEqual]", 
   StyleBox["L", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f916dc93-0893-43dd-b16b-38ec2a780010"],
 " with infinite walls has stationary states ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["x", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{"2", "/", 
     StyleBox["L", "TI"]}]], " ", 
   StyleBox["sin",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "\[Pi]", 
    StyleBox["x", "TI"], "/", 
    StyleBox["L", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "acece6b9-298e-4342-9a63-af0ba4d4a0b8"],
 " and energies ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   SuperscriptBox["\[Pi]", "2"], 
   SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], "/", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"2", 
    StyleBox["m", "TI"], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["L", "TI"], "2"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "865d0861-d1e5-441f-a482-3aefc916a612"],
 ". The physics worth keeping is the ",
 StyleBox["scaling",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "14d35690-3ea4-4209-a32a-a65eba44eeae"],
 "-th level sits at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1daf115b-ce19-40e6-a17c-b95323afce01"],
 " times the ground energy."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3dfd1a96-81f8-4fad-a067-9a2c95e9a1b7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We do not discretize this by hand. The Wolfram Language has a native \
quantum operator for exactly this problem: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "SchrodingerPDEComponent"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "6d335b58-afe1-423b-9580-777210c1c1b6"],
 " assembles the differential operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"-", 
   FractionBox[
    SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], 
    RowBox[{"2", 
     StyleBox["m", "TI"]}]], 
   SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"], "+", 
   StyleBox["V", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["x", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a7f88467-9a9d-409f-80f1-3142d462e5b0"],
 " from physical parameters, and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "NDEigensystem"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "4c81e9c3-bbf1-42e3-ae41-f29c63552fff"],
 " finds its eigenvalues and eigenstates under the boundary conditions we \
impose. The infinite walls are a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "DirichletCondition"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "e5665e50-d19f-495b-8cc2-cd63142c95cb"],
 " forcing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"], "=", "0"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "99e87cbb-0b77-4979-9365-b92217a0b50a"],
 " at the edges of the box. Set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[HBar]", "=", 
   StyleBox["m", "TI"], "=", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b44003a5-1e51-4275-aa70-aebfab09120e"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["V", "TI"], "=", "0"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "60be952e-19cb-4bad-bb90-4129088a9dce"],
 " inside, and solve on ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "52dbd5a1-38b5-499a-9639-8bcf1d349a37"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8206528a-6409-4835-bbf0-7ee57dbe891b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Hbox", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"SchrodingerPDEComponent", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "[", "x", "]"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"{", "x", "}"}]}], "}"}], ",", "\n", "   ", 
     RowBox[{"<|", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<Mass\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "1"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<ReducedPlanckConstant\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "1"}], ",", 
       " ", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<SchrodingerPotential\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "0"}]}], 
      "|>"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"energies", ",", " ", "modes"}], "}"}], " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"NDEigensystem", "[", "\n", "   ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"Hbox", ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"DirichletCondition", "[", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "[", "x", "]"}], " ", "==", " ", "0"}], ",", " ", 
         "True"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "[", "x", "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], ",", " ", "5"}], 
    "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", "energies"}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[2]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"4304c218-4cb1-401e-8b03-d45070fa5a90"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
  "4.934806367856982`", ",", "19.739474484147934`", ",", "44.41622688824364`",
    ",", "78.97358311901903`", ",", "123.43323782051375`"}], "}"}]], "Output",\

 CellLabel->"Out[2]= ",ExpressionUUID->"8df05636-02c4-46a7-8b7d-41c36266e7ea"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This returns ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
   "4.93", ",", " ", "19.74", ",", " ", "44.42", ",", " ", "78.97", ",", " ", 
    "123.43"}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "7785eccf-3078-4aa5-a88f-d203de7e8446"],
 ", matching the exact ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["E", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["k", "TI"]], "=", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["k", "TI"], "2"], 
    SuperscriptBox["\[Pi]", "2"], "/", 
    StyleBox["(",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    RowBox[{"2", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["L", "TI"], "2"]}], 
    StyleBox[")",
     SpanMaxSize->1], "=", "{", "4.93"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], "19.74", 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], "44.41", 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], "78.96", 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"123.37", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4bf12187-ee1a-41f3-82f3-6c21894506bb"],
 " to better than a part in a thousand, with no hand-built matrix anywhere."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c80802ff-8954-4efd-906d-2452c63451f2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The clean physical statement is the ratio. Verify that the levels scale as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["k", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "630941a4-c056-455c-baa1-67eb25a3bf21"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"89c3f673-e19a-4fa9-9096-1fb8c4a4a6d2"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"energies", "/", 
  RowBox[{"First", "[", "energies", "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[3]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"92756235-9e0f-4b17-a6bb-54bfd54e4da2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
  "1.`", ",", "4.000050460484453`", ",", "9.000601761712506`", ",", 
   "16.00338032175203`", ",", "25.0127823909161`"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[3]= ",ExpressionUUID->"c311f6dd-4a4f-4431-a6b3-689b4c6943d6"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The result ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
   "1.", ",", " ", "4.00", ",", " ", "9.00", ",", " ", "16.00", ",", " ", 
    "25.01"}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "4d820ef2-6a37-46c1-9c76-85621928bdea"],
 " is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "1"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"4", ",", "9", ",", "16"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"25", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6d10da82-f139-4edf-b392-462036d080bd"],
 ". The boundary condition alone forces the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["k", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c3cb1161-9425-4b6b-b99f-3d7a1e4ab922"],
 " ladder."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4b558b89-06ff-4d18-85b1-cc6cd6ab6f9f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Each eigenstate is a continuous wavefunction. To bring it into \
QuantumFramework, which works in finite-dimensional Hilbert spaces, sample it \
on a grid and hand the values to a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumState"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "17ef9233-e948-44f4-b80d-dc38ef835aa4"],
 ", which normalizes them into a unit vector:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"454e38a1-3a69-4a68-806d-3ca5164f1aff"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"grid", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Subdivide", "[", 
    RowBox[{"0.", ",", " ", "1.", ",", " ", "64"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"ground", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"modes", "[", 
          RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], " ", "/.", " ", 
         RowBox[{"x", " ", "->", " ", "#"}]}], ")"}], " ", "&"}], " ", "/@", 
      " ", "grid"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<Normalize\>\"", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"ground", "[", "\"\<Norm\>\"", "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[4]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"7ccc0482-3d2e-4e82-80a9-3460f3c41328"],

Cell[BoxData["0.9999999999999999`"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[4]= ",ExpressionUUID->"a0cffda6-2719-48f2-88da-9687b02af08a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ground", "[", "\"\<Norm\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"a2a55281-fad1-4701-b4ba-34a82073d743"],
 " is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "1."], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "5465b929-698d-40b5-9dea-99496bd5dcfa"],
 ": a genuine normalized state, its amplitudes the half-sine ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["sin",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"\[Pi]", 
    StyleBox["x", "TI"], "/", 
    StyleBox["L", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a2caf1f2-2009-423e-aa43-934480e3d88a"],
 " peaked at the center of the box."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a167cd77-585f-4f4f-894f-58c256c89b6c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is the bridge for the whole document. A continuous wave-mechanics \
problem was solved natively, and its ground state became a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumState"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "65e4ed0e-91a0-4c2c-920f-e73880d8a61c"],
 ". From here on we work in finite-dimensional Hilbert spaces, where the \
language is pure linear algebra. (The finite-well version, where the walls \
are a finite barrier, is a worked example at the end.)"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"905e30ba-1c2f-47d6-ae50-fd90ef74e60e"],

Cell["Part 2: States, observables, and measurement", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"17620af8-b809-476e-8764-f8d3cd8ff9a5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A pure quantum state is a unit vector. The smallest interesting case is the \
qubit, a two-level system. In Dirac notation we write kets like ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "aa41cc9c-1731-4b7e-87fc-c3003bc681cd"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "55c1fead-2420-4820-ab43-b353d6407508"],
 " for the computational basis and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{"+"},
    "Ket"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"0"},
       "Ket"], "+", 
      TemplateBox[{"1"},
       "Ket"]}], ")"}], "/", 
    SqrtBox["2"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a164d5ca-d560-44cd-acc5-a17346558951"],
 " for an equal superposition. Build a few and look at one:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7f900ff9-7868-4198-9781-3c60d3fef7e4"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"zero", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<0\>\"", "]"}]}], ";", " ", 
  RowBox[{"one", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<1\>\"", "]"}]}], ";", " ", 
  RowBox[{"plus", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"psi", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "I"}], "}"}], "/", 
     RowBox[{"Sqrt", "[", "2", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"psi", "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "Normal"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[5]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"a963215b-48a1-4574-a962-8158c9769738"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], ",", 
   FractionBox["\[ImaginaryI]", 
    SqrtBox["2"]]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[5]= ",ExpressionUUID->"684c9605-ccb2-4123-b78e-27fc920fb7ed"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This returns ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", "1", "/", 
     SqrtBox["2"]}], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["i", "TI"], "/", 
     SqrtBox["2"]}]}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "004c1d28-9f09-4e71-9b3f-0f0704beaa2a"],
 ". The state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "psi"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "baea5781-7d0d-4681-a70f-1afe771d7a61"],
 " is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"0"},
      "Ket"], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
      TemplateBox[{"1"},
       "Ket"]}]}], ")"}], "/", 
   SqrtBox["2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ae7ca0b3-ef40-4f05-b6f7-89fdf7e35438"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"psi", "[", "\"\<Norm\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "64aa51c2-3888-43a0-be9f-27a9ea46662f"],
 " is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "1"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"1dc49dbf-5cd3-468e-bb70-5130b6836932"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"14f077ea-5fd3-45d5-b62b-5f7d39f1261c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 StyleBox["bra",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
   "Bra"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ad440feb-427e-4e20-a864-97b69eca6bc7"],
 " is the conjugate-transpose of the ket, obtained with the ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<Dagger\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "cd97bfd3-6526-4fb0-81ad-a39dde85946d"],
 " property. The inner product ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Phi]", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
   "BraKet"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d19d99b7-e5e5-4a94-8a12-d69647639ff4"],
 " is then a bra applied to a ket, and its numerical value is the ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<Scalar\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "49d0d122-97ad-4121-a29b-8c7bf08e0d30"],
 " of the resulting zero-qudit object. Compute ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0", "+"},
   "BraKet"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ff2e40d8-c47d-4b0e-863a-14620d1ed754"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f7d11021-7218-4ece-b7f3-23e39d0565ac"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"(", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"zero", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", "plus"}], 
   ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[6]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"ac559972-3834-4b6d-a3df-a31f35e3fbf6"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox["1", 
  SqrtBox["2"]]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[6]= ",ExpressionUUID->"67fdeb9d-8136-4d18-adf6-50b7885a6509"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The answer is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "/", 
   SqrtBox["2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c39c11f4-5f2c-4681-b658-3208b9ffd6f8"],
 ", the overlap of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3eacb2e2-e291-4646-abbe-c1c31ca46066"],
 " with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"+"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "33d02464-f3ae-4a1a-82b7-4d645a30ce45"],
 ". This single idiom, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"bra", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", "ket"}], 
    ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "7aecad83-f0e1-4723-b803-8f8b518444ab"],
 ", is how we extract every amplitude, overlap, and expectation value below."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b1318b5f-e680-467d-83b6-434b0026ffe3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "An ",
 StyleBox["observable",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " is a Hermitian operator. The Pauli operators ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ece7c44c-aeeb-4def-b10a-8bb42a55d219"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Y", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "978a7b3e-f66b-4d01-85c8-b941b71be4f5"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2d1c92b2-b998-41ff-8367-c5d4ed8edeb9"],
 " are the basic qubit observables. Look at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7569e06c-f28d-453e-8389-3e5f5f023426"],
 " and confirm it is Hermitian with real eigenvalues ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "284c0d54-55fc-4d40-abfd-f3330a294b09"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3f648835-d460-473c-b82b-fe351f42f05d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Z", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Z\>\"", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Z", "[", "\"\<HermitianQ\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Z", "[", "\"\<Eigenvalues\>\"", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[7]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"422c29e8-6498-4e0e-b0d0-6152d4d5fe75"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"True", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", "1"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[7]= ",ExpressionUUID->"b61eb876-55f4-4cf8-a6e0-82bcc112fd3f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This returns ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"True", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"95a14f3e-2bef-41a0-8c8d-984fccb0daf4"],
 ": we ask the operator whether it is Hermitian rather than pulling out its \
matrix and testing by hand. The eigenvalues are the possible measurement \
outcomes; the eigenvectors ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{"0"},
    "Ket"], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   TemplateBox[{"1"},
    "Ket"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bacf1c87-8b02-4241-bd40-449cff173404"],
 " are the states that yield those outcomes with certainty. Hermiticity is \
exactly the guarantee that the outcomes are real."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3be08617-4416-4ae6-adf0-a7b31db3bc83"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 StyleBox["expectation value",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{
     StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
    "Bra"], 
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
   TemplateBox[{
     StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
    "Ket"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "21195336-92eb-4d11-ac53-2e0128e62ad9"],
 " is the mean outcome of measuring ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["A", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "94f0e6be-68d9-4871-a6c3-e713ca35e1e3"],
 " in state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "51a2b5fc-0dce-4570-b14d-1b213d2ba8bd"],
 ". There are several equivalent ways to compute it, and seeing them agree \
builds confidence. Compute ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"+", "\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
     StyleBox["Z", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], 
    "+"}], 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9c531b31-c651-48c6-9c3c-b293c85479fa"],
 " three ways, by a trace, by a bra-operator-ket sandwich, and by an explicit \
measurement:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f8e6b1ca-9432-4d6b-b26e-b01ded94dff9"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"{", "\n", "  ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Tr", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Z", "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", "]"}], " ", ".", " ", 
      RowBox[{"plus", "[", "\"\<DensityMatrix\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", "\n",
     "  ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"plus", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", 
       RowBox[{"Z", " ", "@", " ", "plus"}]}], ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", 
     "]"}], ",", "\n", "  ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"QuantumMeasurementOperator", "[", "Z", "]"}], "[", "plus", 
      "]"}], "[", "\"\<Mean\>\"", "]"}]}], "\n", "}"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "Chop"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[8]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"70e6b014-6f91-4e1b-b057-aee43eba39b4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[8]= ",ExpressionUUID->"738d5164-df7f-4031-90b6-997b3f4f2650"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "All three return ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "0"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"19bf669a-08f3-4412-b2d9-cd4c961475f3"],
 ". In the state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"+"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bf1ad470-d1d7-4711-92df-b7ff8c613fc4"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8fcfed2b-001c-42bb-ae1e-c4f23f695d53"],
 " is equally likely to give ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c2d9e8e2-0e06-4b34-a3ca-e73eab8bc6d1"],
 " or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3ea7dff9-7aa0-4010-8bce-5e91f12d8229"],
 ", so its mean is zero."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a9876034-6dad-426a-bbc0-4bcbb0634143"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Measurement is more than its mean: it is a probability distribution over \
eigenvalues. Apply a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "97b80f62-1fdf-4f74-9d25-af505f8bafaf"],
 " measurement to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"+"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8aa5ed5d-06a1-40a7-bdf2-1e387de744d7"],
 " and read the outcome probabilities:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a5953a19-2260-4ee1-a936-1b6049f68753"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"qm", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"QuantumMeasurementOperator", "[", "\"\<Z\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
    "plus", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Values", "[", 
  RowBox[{"qm", "[", "\"\<Probabilities\>\"", "]"}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[9]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"996a3018-3aac-42f0-9c60-42e76decf766"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", "2"], ",", 
   FractionBox["1", "2"]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[9]= ",ExpressionUUID->"88268ba9-0c85-4c1a-9950-5571085d2f9f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The result is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "1", "/", "2"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"1", "/", "2", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "72c2f6c9-7f27-488b-a243-8b746c1770ee"],
 ". This is the Born rule in action: the probability of an outcome is the \
squared overlap of the state with the corresponding eigenvector."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3e994e64-fa2b-4365-b691-3688fe855909"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 StyleBox["uncertainty principle",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " quantifies how unsharp two incompatible observables must be. The Robertson \
relation says ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], "\[CapitalDelta]", 
   StyleBox["B", "TI"], "\[GreaterEqual]", 
   FractionBox["1", "2"], "\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   StyleBox["B", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "27d9851e-1181-4c79-a2c2-68ee5a64634a"],
 ", where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], "=", 
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["A", "TI"], "2"], 
     StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1], "-", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
        SpanMaxSize->1], 
       StyleBox["A", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
       StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
        SpanMaxSize->1]}], "2"]}]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c21953e5-e5d6-4a8c-b025-51f88950f44f"],
 ". We do not hand-roll the variance: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"OperatorVariance", "[", 
   RowBox[{"state", ",", " ", "op"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "6278316c-f38f-4310-881f-d74aeb327882"],
 " is exactly ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["O", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "-", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     StyleBox["O", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
     StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}], "2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "744b234c-6d85-457d-81e4-6b2f80cf732a"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"Commutator", "[", 
   RowBox[{"A", ",", " ", "B"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "04a8cc5c-f318-42f6-8da7-474eff26036e"],
 " is the built-in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["B", "TI"], "-", 
   StyleBox["B", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["A", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "704391c4-8c28-4767-8dc4-60b08743dd50"],
 ". Check the relation for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "56902f03-4131-41eb-8268-290ed8db6b54"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Y", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8297e884-9719-4a7b-b6d4-799a170d5eb6"],
 " on a generic complex state, one tilted off all three axes so the bound \
actually bites:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a9179f87-36f9-42a9-be91-144f03d12dac"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"st", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
       RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "8"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Exp", "[", 
        RowBox[{"I", " ", 
         RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "5"}]}], "]"}], " ", 
       RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
        RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "8"}], "]"}]}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"X", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<X\>\"", "]"}]}], ";", " ", 
  RowBox[{"Y", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Y\>\"", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Sqrt", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"OperatorVariance", "[", 
        RowBox[{"st", ",", " ", "X"}], "]"}], " ", 
       RowBox[{"OperatorVariance", "[", 
        RowBox[{"st", ",", " ", "Y"}], "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", "\n", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Abs", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"st", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"Commutator", "[", 
            RowBox[{"X", ",", " ", "Y"}], "]"}], " ", "@", " ", "st"}]}], 
         ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], "/", "2"}]}], "}"}], " ",
    "//", " ", "N"}], " ", "//", " ", "Chop"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[10]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"21918038-9748-4fe0-8bac-f5fe4381302b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.7460105770525087`", ",", "0.7071067811865475`"}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[10]= ",ExpressionUUID->"845552c6-1701-4a89-ae9a-a7594ce4e539"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This returns ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"0.746", ",", " ", "0.707"}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"0f39742b-338b-4bdf-9cbc-cbcfa492050e"],
 ": the product of spreads exceeds the bound ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", "2"], "\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   StyleBox["Y", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "\[RightBracketingBar]", "=", "\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fc462e90-3ed4-4a33-b6ec-2c788f01c989"],
 ", and the inequality is strict. For a pure qubit state the exact relation \
is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], "2"], " ", "\[CapitalDelta]", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["Y", "TI"], "2"], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     StyleBox["Z", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
     StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}], "2"], "+", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     StyleBox["X", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
     StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}], "2"], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     StyleBox["Y", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
     StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}], "2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "872570a1-8bd8-4ea0-b6cc-6eebbbc3c604"],
 ", so the bound is reached only when one of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
    StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1]}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    StyleBox["Y", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
    StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b6b69bea-7359-4253-a455-22ef62c8e708"],
 " vanishes. Here neither does, so the state cannot even saturate the limit. \
The inequality is never violated, which is the whole content of the \
uncertainty principle: you cannot make both spreads small when the \
observables fail to commute. (Part 5 will show the oscillator's ground state \
hitting the bound exactly.)"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d0bc2fe8-8ddd-4b36-b51b-a88dc607b72c"],

Cell["Before moving on, the key results so far, all computed:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9258532d-ea96-4e61-94f8-296c16a85bf0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A pure qubit state is a unit vector; the bra is its conjugate transpose, \
obtained with ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<Dagger\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "bf3ab48f-4ea7-4f27-a746-d6ffea4a5635"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"44ff5fe1-0952-4706-8c28-733589e22c9b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Inner products, amplitudes, and expectation values all reduce to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"bra", " ", "@", " ", "ket"}], ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", 
   "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "ad81bf99-12f0-4555-8d45-78ffbdabe2d1"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"f28ca7d4-088f-4bc7-844a-2de6cf27c108"],

Cell["\<\
Observables are Hermitian operators; their eigenvalues are the outcomes and \
are real.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"128af2bf-41f6-480a-9c49-ab2a006c4010"],

Cell["\<\
Measurement returns a Born-rule probability distribution, not just a number.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"54100fde-9fb8-44d5-bdfb-c3ee7fd891e4"],

Cell["\<\
Non-commuting observables obey the Robertson uncertainty bound.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"69b16cfc-d117-4432-bb2e-a854cb848dc2"],

Cell["Part 3: Dynamics and the three pictures", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"191bbc45-244c-4e77-88c4-a480e6579acf"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A closed quantum system evolves by the Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger equation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[PartialD]", 
      StyleBox["t", "TI"]], 
     TemplateBox[{
       StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
      "Ket"]}]}], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["H", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e5881099-6a8e-441c-aabb-724f97bfad9d"],
 ", whose solution is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{
     RowBox[{
       StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"], 
       StyleBox["(", SpanMaxSize -> 1], 
       StyleBox["t", "TI"], 
       StyleBox[")", SpanMaxSize -> 1]}]},
    "Ket"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
     RowBox[{"-", 
      StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
      StyleBox["H", "TI"], 
      StyleBox["t", "TI"]}]], 
    TemplateBox[{
      RowBox[{
        StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"], 
        StyleBox["(", SpanMaxSize -> 1], "0", 
        StyleBox[")", SpanMaxSize -> 1]}]},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7cde307e-462e-46a4-9654-db074ba8dadc"],
 ". ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumEvolve"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "74b5467f-4a27-4b00-8fd9-28fb53e2f745"],
 " solves this for us. Called with no time range, it returns a ",
 StyleBox["closed-form symbolic",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " state, which is the cleanest thing to learn from. Evolve ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"+"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "21269546-b12f-48ba-a903-c99328331c8f"],
 " under ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["H", "TI"], "=", 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "466e6d1f-bd23-445c-9379-b07046fcec8a"],
 " (free precession of a spin in a field along ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "246c7b6e-8ab8-4853-b34c-811cfc18acc6"],
 "):"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ac5a2c74-e3ee-4fb8-845c-d5f8db30a628"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"sol", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEvolve", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Z\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"sol", "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
   "Normal"}], " ", "//", " ", "Simplify"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[11]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"32528dff-1d0a-4aed-b3f9-48a8fa5b3b5d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox[
    SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[ImaginaryI]"}], " ", "\[FormalT]"}]], 
    SqrtBox["2"]], ",", 
   FractionBox[
    SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
     RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[FormalT]"}]], 
    SqrtBox["2"]]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[11]= ",ExpressionUUID->"40e987b8-7a17-4fbb-a5fc-7a1e727a6ec5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The result is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
      RowBox[{"-", 
       StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
       StyleBox["t", "TI"]}]], "/", 
     SqrtBox["2"]}], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], "\[ThickSpace]", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
      StyleBox[
       RowBox[{"i", "t"}], "TI"]], "/", 
     SqrtBox["2"]}]}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "058bae83-6e46-4904-9637-e4646ecfdb12"],
 ", with the framework using a formal time symbol. The two amplitudes acquire \
opposite phases, so the state rotates around the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "accb3107-abe7-4d23-9681-50fe2830964d"],
 "-axis of the Bloch sphere at angular frequency ",
 Cell[BoxData["2"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "cfee4f04-720f-494e-bfbd-9032fa4b007e"],
 ". This is Larmor precession, derived with one line."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bd3568cb-c13e-4026-9bcd-0a10ecf0ce13"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "When a closed form is unavailable or unwanted, give ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumEvolve"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a560a813-2881-4353-8d1b-9e4b37e34a64"],
 " a numeric time range and it integrates the equation, returning a state you \
sample at any time with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"sol", "[", 
   RowBox[{"<|", 
    RowBox[{"t", " ", "->", " ", "value"}], "|>"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"728cef8d-c76a-4c0c-8332-b44adb1f0f71"],
 ". We use that form in the next two parts."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f06da184-818f-47e6-beb5-ecc316a17432"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 StyleBox["three pictures",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " are three bookkeeping conventions for the same physics. In the Schr\
\[ODoubleDot]dinger picture the state moves and operators are fixed. In the \
Heisenberg picture the state is fixed and operators move as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["t", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
    StyleBox[
     RowBox[{"i", "H", "t"}], "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], " ", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{"-", 
     StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["H", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["t", "TI"]}]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8fe44e16-c3cc-498e-b76c-ea05ece7d78f"],
 ". Expectation values, the only measurable quantities, are identical in \
both. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumEvolve"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "bdfa3fac-bc8b-450c-a9f5-a2da8f4b3d6f"],
 " handles either: pass it a state and it moves the state; pass it an \
observable (with an empty Lindblad list ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", "}"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "01e29aee-ac64-4962-ad38-50fd90842aa3"],
 ") and it returns the Heisenberg-evolved operator. Compute ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["(",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    StyleBox["t", "TI"], 
    StyleBox[")",
     SpanMaxSize->1]}], 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "17cff460-bad9-439f-96c5-ffca3ea87a39"],
 " under ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["H", "TI"], "=", 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fc8e672b-79f7-4f80-a2b9-5464bb55cb3a"],
 " both ways:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c129ae30-3baa-4773-824e-83b68c8a8052"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"H", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Z\>\"", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"schrod", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEvolve", "[", 
    RowBox[{"H", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"xSchrodinger", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"schrod", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<X\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", 
         "schrod"}]}], ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
     "ComplexExpand"}], " ", "//", " ", "Simplify"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Xt", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEvolve", "[", 
    RowBox[{"H", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<X\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"xHeisenberg", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}], 
         "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", 
        RowBox[{"Xt", " ", "@", " ", 
         RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}]}]}], ")"}], 
      "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", "ComplexExpand"}], " ", "//",
     " ", "Simplify"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"xSchrodinger", ",", " ", "xHeisenberg"}], "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[12]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"f95fa182-4c24-4a62-a23d-15fa7ce21ce7"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
    RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[FormalT]"}], "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
    RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[FormalT]"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[12]= ",ExpressionUUID->"96c1e41f-5d0c-4c5e-a820-aabb43157cf8"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Both return ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["cos",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"2", 
    StyleBox["t", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "29b86150-df67-4d21-b7cd-c7b94a62c8d9"],
 ": the expectation of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "512dd50f-8213-4097-b075-782dba9456ea"],
 " oscillates as the state precesses, and the Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger and \
Heisenberg computations agree identically. The interaction picture, \
introduced next for the driven qubit, is the same idea applied to the part of \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["H", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d70fe0bb-d8dd-4b82-86c9-a78dd7e0d0bb"],
 " we already understand, leaving only the interesting interaction in the \
equations."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cb855e0d-6d3f-4626-8b7f-49e8559d227e"],

Cell["Part 4: The qubit and Rabi flopping", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"042fb864-4b43-4d79-8385-cdfa9bcde3a4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A two-level atom driven by a resonant classical field, viewed in the \
interaction picture, has the simple Hamiltonian ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["H", "TI"], "=", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"\[CapitalOmega]", "/", "2"}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], " ", 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "47cd6754-45f8-4c89-871d-cceb0288f937"],
 ", where ",
 Cell[BoxData["\[CapitalOmega]"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6fed8471-c915-40b9-b140-be385da5d77e"],
 " is the Rabi frequency set by the drive strength. Starting in the ground \
state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6feee2a5-01ac-4ece-abf5-98b1b3afa245"],
 ", the population sloshes coherently to the excited state and back. Evolve \
symbolically and read the amplitudes:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6bc5ae9f-5262-46d9-9907-d8ef460f32fe"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalOmega]", " ", "=", " ", "1"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Hdrive", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"\[CapitalOmega]", "/", "2"}], ")"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<X\>\"", "]"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"rabi", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEvolve", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Hdrive", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<0\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"rabi", "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
   "Normal"}], " ", "//", " ", "Simplify"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[13]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"fdf66ce9-31c6-429d-a1ed-c161885c1339"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
    FractionBox["\[FormalT]", "2"], "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", "\[ImaginaryI]"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
     FractionBox["\[FormalT]", "2"], "]"}]}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[13]= ",ExpressionUUID->"29f06b87-b91d-4fe4-8457-8a6822e59dfe"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The state is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      StyleBox["cos",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
      StyleBox["(",
       SpanMaxSize->1], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["t", "TI"], "/", "2"}], 
      StyleBox[")",
       SpanMaxSize->1]}], 
     RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}]}], " ", "-", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["sin",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["(",
       SpanMaxSize->1], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["t", "TI"], "/", "2"}], 
      StyleBox[")",
       SpanMaxSize->1]}]}]}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0dc95eaf-40bf-4516-9d6d-7b590be1cbdd"],
 " (with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalOmega]", "=", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "23ef6ca5-87b2-4e02-b86e-269d10e6a595"],
 "). The excited-state probability is therefore ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P", "TI"], "1"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["t", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"\[CapitalOmega]", 
    StyleBox["t", "TI"], "/", "2"}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "72d1f200-238e-42a9-a25f-f9d7e1a1bbb7"],
 ": complete, periodic population transfer. A pulse of duration ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["t", "TI"], "=", "\[Pi]", "/", "\[CapitalOmega]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bfbf563c-00f7-4f70-92ff-5e195028f8c7"],
 " is a ",
 Cell[BoxData["\[Pi]"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "150fb964-51d8-4de3-b442-1d56cdd3fc2a"],
 "-pulse, which flips ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c13150ec-b271-4a85-84e3-95ad216168aa"],
 " to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d6b54380-6d55-4f69-ab4a-bbf07a2484f8"],
 "; a pulse of half that is a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "22811748-7894-417d-890e-230869185fef"],
 "-pulse, which builds an equal superposition. These are the elementary \
control operations of every qubit platform."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"07a6b8af-7035-41a0-8a99-08ee00f4571e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Real drives are never perfectly on resonance. With a detuning ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Delta]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "db6463eb-f155-4961-8440-98f297305e3f"],
 " between the drive and the qubit, the interaction-picture Hamiltonian gains \
a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d3242981-ca31-44fa-8ff1-5e5ecf874d9d"],
 "-term: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["H", "TI"], "=", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"\[CapitalOmega]", "/", "2"}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], "+", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Delta]", "TI"], "/", "2"}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e6bd1c1f-4066-4a35-900e-07d35cbce136"],
 ". Evolve and extract the excited-state probability as a function of time \
and detuning:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9ada4abf-f66e-4057-aa69-245986c0d331"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Hdet", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], ")"}], " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<X\>\"", "]"}]}], " ", "+", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Delta]", "/", "2"}], ")"}], " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Z\>\"", "]"}]}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"rabiDet", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEvolve", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Hdet", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<0\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"sv", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"rabiDet", "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
    "Normal"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Abs", "[", 
     RowBox[{"sv", "[", 
      RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], "^", "2"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Assumptions", " ", "->", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Delta]", " ", "\[Element]", " ", "Reals"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\[FormalT]", " ", "\[Element]", " ", "Reals"}]}], "}"}]}]}], 
  "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[14]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"dd8cf0a5-d484-4f43-bf11-a0b59a5fa02d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox[
  SuperscriptBox[
   RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["1", "2"], " ", "\[FormalT]", " ", 
     SqrtBox[
      RowBox[{"1", "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["\[Delta]", "2"]}]]}], "]"}], "2"], 
  RowBox[{"1", "+", 
   SuperscriptBox["\[Delta]", "2"]}]]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[14]= ",ExpressionUUID->"92819320-9268-41a5-8739-899ca3144dd3"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["The framework returns", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6022fad7-7001-4f43-8676-89a3cd7a6458"],

Cell[BoxData[
 PaneBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["P", "TI"], "1"], 
    StyleBox["(",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    StyleBox["t", "TI"], 
    StyleBox[")",
     SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["sin",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], "\[ThinSpace]", "\[NegativeThinSpace]", 
      StyleBox["(",
       FontSize->1.2 Inherited], 
      FractionBox[
       StyleBox["t", "TI"], "2"], 
      SqrtBox[
       RowBox[{"1", "+", 
        SuperscriptBox[
         StyleBox["\[Delta]", "TI"], "2"]}]], 
      StyleBox[")",
       FontSize->1.2 Inherited]}], 
     RowBox[{"1", "+", 
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["\[Delta]", "TI"], "2"]}]]}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}]}],
  Alignment->Center,
  ImageSize->Full]], "DisplayFormula",ExpressionUUID->"a8c00941-8db7-464d-\
84ae-4d9b61601eb1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "which (with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalOmega]", "=", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8c9e9a5f-525d-4537-8222-d62939b771fe"],
 ", so ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Delta]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "388441f4-4865-4a32-95e3-b7f2125cdc79"],
 " is measured in units of ",
 Cell[BoxData["\[CapitalOmega]"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e1897d6d-f613-4460-85b7-5dd69a6baf0c"],
 ") is exactly the textbook detuned Rabi formula ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P", "TI"], "1"], "=", 
   FractionBox[
    SuperscriptBox["\[CapitalOmega]", "2"], 
    SubsuperscriptBox["\[CapitalOmega]", 
     StyleBox["R", "TI"], "2"]], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[CapitalOmega]", 
     StyleBox["R", "TI"]], 
    StyleBox["t", "TI"], "/", "2"}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "eddcf9fe-2705-4f52-a68a-2c5a2b0947bb"],
 " with generalized Rabi frequency ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[CapitalOmega]", 
    StyleBox["R", "TI"]], "=", 
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["\[CapitalOmega]", "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["\[Delta]", "TI"], "2"]}]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d5bbbc53-9bfe-4fc2-8eb8-a8a2992f3b1c"],
 ". Two things are visible at a glance: detuning ",
 StyleBox["speeds up",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " the oscillation (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[CapitalOmega]", 
    StyleBox["R", "TI"]], ">", "\[CapitalOmega]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "045cd524-051c-4451-aa9d-fa5ed7fe6041"],
 ") and ",
 StyleBox["caps its amplitude",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " below ",
 Cell[BoxData["1"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2f531068-db7b-4854-bf5a-974cd955d138"],
 " (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P", "TI"], "1", 
    StyleBox["max",
     FontSlant->"Plain"]], "=", "1", "/", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"1", "+", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["\[Delta]", "TI"], "2"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d520ad96-e96b-48b0-a3bf-ef0239c999bf"],
 "). You can no longer fully invert the qubit once you are off resonance."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"470d7158-b997-4dc2-b3f0-ba3a3e980b79"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The natural picture for a qubit is the ",
 StyleBox["Bloch sphere",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", where a pure state is a point on a unit sphere and a mixed state lies \
inside it. The Bloch vector is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
    StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1]}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    StyleBox["Y", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
    StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1]}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    StyleBox["Z", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
    StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
     SpanMaxSize->1]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d59e32f1-c102-4b78-a0cb-f27234a012e1"],
 ". Read it for a state at polar angle ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "3"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9546d2ee-4c71-425c-a2e2-b574aa25f8a7"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8ad9494b-b024-4ab8-8b10-2e893a120d31"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
      RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "6"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
      RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "6"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], "]"}], 
  "[", "\"\<BlochVector\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[15]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"45280f24-53fa-4636-8d97-3d9f0bb33fbf"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox[
    SqrtBox["3"], "2"], ",", "0", ",", 
   FractionBox["1", "2"]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[15]= ",ExpressionUUID->"419e4daf-d2da-4168-9f29-38296382beb5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The result is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     SqrtBox["3"], "/", "2"}], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], " ", "0", 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f98c4232-cf7d-48f5-98d4-bb279b2b76aa"],
 ", a unit vector tilted ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["60", "\[SmallCircle]"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f58cab00-8583-4593-8ad1-34669a536a8b"],
 " from the north pole. The framework will also draw it for you with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
       RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "6"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "6"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], "]"}], 
   "[", "\"\<BlochPlot\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "8851d8df-c9fe-4081-9619-933dce0e83de"],
 ". Under the resonant drive of this section, this arrow simply rotates about \
the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4f96f609-fa5f-48ed-b5c7-fc50b617ba7c"],
 "-axis; Rabi flopping ",
 StyleBox["is", "TI"],
 " that rotation, seen in the populations."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c55ffb49-51c0-4651-a656-87142dbc1aaf"],

Cell["Part 5: The quantum harmonic oscillator", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2e3e9bf5-c227-4053-b157-193fde5541cd"],

Cell["\<\
This part uses the second-quantization sub-package loaded in Setup.\
\>", "Text",
 CellFrame->{{3, 0}, {0, 0}},
 CellMargins->{{40, 10}, {7, 7}},
 CellFrameMargins->10,
 CellFrameColor->GrayLevel[0.55],
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 FontColor->LightDarkSwitched[
   GrayLevel[0.45], 
   GrayLevel[0.65]],
 Background->LightDarkSwitched[
   GrayLevel[0.96], 
   GrayLevel[0.2]],ExpressionUUID->"08e26bb5-5eff-4e25-9811-73f5499f9ee0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The harmonic oscillator is the other system every quantum engineer must \
own, because it models a mode of the electromagnetic field in a cavity and a \
mechanical resonator alike. Its algebra is built from the lowering operator \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["a", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bfe0404f-05ca-40fc-8dd5-1bd0fff54e7c"],
 " and raising operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "faff6d75-ae87-4331-aef0-388ea1b58206"],
 ", with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "043b9b56-e2ce-4546-8dcd-d9163ea941f9"],
 ". In a truncated Fock space of size ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["N", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4b3bc647-c5fb-4e40-b0ae-8d1d520613ce"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"AnnihilationOperator", "[", "N", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"7ed471ae-b202-48a9-8f40-b8058fc924a5"],
 " is the matrix with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SqrtBox[
   StyleBox["k", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bbf52e3b-fb54-4fc7-b2b8-524203afd9d1"],
 " on the first super-diagonal:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1537d047-f928-4ee4-adac-90a757adb387"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"a", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"AnnihilationOperator", "[", "5", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"a", "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "Normal"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[16]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"748f166c-0c57-4704-b31a-7a07d6540535"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "1", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", 
     SqrtBox["2"], ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", 
     SqrtBox["3"], ",", "0"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "2"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "}"}]}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[16]= ",ExpressionUUID->"6fc8c2b7-3a0a-4d87-b12f-c7de788d0cac"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The number operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "^"], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"], 
   StyleBox["a", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0bf99d77-d290-4137-bf84-9a782b89be33"],
 " counts excitations, and its diagonal is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"0", ",", "1", ",", "2"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], "\[Ellipsis]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "32120bcc-0fb8-4df2-bf29-88e0f6027dba"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"53ee39c8-b3bd-4f0d-a09d-d2679f91b296"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Diagonal", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Normal", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"a", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", "a"}], ")"}], 
    "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[17]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"24202014-4ff6-4ab9-9ed2-c89813f9b703"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0", ",", "1", ",", "2", ",", "3", ",", "4"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[17]= ",ExpressionUUID->"382fdaf2-4c5f-484e-9f56-0f6a1e9b71d6"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This returns ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "2", ",", " ", "3", ",", " ", "4"}], 
   "}"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "25aed9d5-9ed3-4a04-9a50-f2bdc57d9013"],
 ". The eigenstates of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  OverscriptBox[
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "^"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c9a607cf-bbd8-4ddb-8bbd-548833583413"],
 " are the ",
 StyleBox["number (Fock) states",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "78bf67a9-ba2f-48c1-8a31-d4d476ffeeea"],
 ", the energy eigenstates of the oscillator. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"FockState", "[", 
   RowBox[{"2", ",", " ", "5"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "6b523fa1-1f7a-440b-9222-a4f104ea4ece"],
 " is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"2"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "91a512b6-3f41-4593-9918-b04a5012ba50"],
 " in a five-level truncation:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"db6e93ca-2f2e-467b-86a2-c2af5d1c7b6e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"FockState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"2", ",", " ", "5"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], 
  " ", "//", " ", "Normal"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[18]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"7d2a89ac-8924-4df0-a218-3c2e03e4325c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", "1", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[18]= ",ExpressionUUID->"ebb3a032-5fec-41a5-93c9-e6145eab2c00"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "which is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0", ",", "1", ",", "0"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0b661729-9db4-446d-8b80-b2c7ade5b499"],
 ", a single excitation count with definite energy."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"186ae454-17bc-49be-bcc1-896aea8252a9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A ",
 StyleBox["coherent state",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "924fdffc-d6d9-47d8-8332-cd8d4e352ba2"],
 " is the closest a quantum oscillator comes to a classical sinusoid: a \
displaced ground state with a Poisson distribution of photon numbers and mean \
occupation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
    StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", "\[RightBracketingBar]"}],
    "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3ad85a7e-9501-434f-b8f3-f036e9d69788"],
 ". In the framework it is built parametrically in a formal amplitude; \
substitute a value to make it concrete:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ed462249-9235-430a-a919-7b3f64f173bf"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"coh", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"CoherentState", "[", "8", "]"}], "[", 
    RowBox[{"<|", 
     RowBox[{"\[FormalAlpha]", " ", "->", " ", "1.0"}], "|>"}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"a8", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"AnnihilationOperator", "[", "8", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"(", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"coh", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"a8", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", "a8"}], 
      ")"}], " ", "@", " ", "coh"}]}], ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", 
  "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[19]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"ab595bfd-11e0-4190-97e1-c9421c5863a1"],

Cell[BoxData["0.99992700729927`"], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[19]= ",ExpressionUUID->"5a256b3f-441d-4d23-b006-9a8fb13c8280"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The mean photon number comes out as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "1.0"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "12c66dc9-c5ee-4260-acfb-06f7839150c6"],
 ", that is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
    StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"], "\[VeryThinSpace]", "\[RightBracketingBar]"}],
    "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0fd0a36e-9d2c-4e6d-aa0a-ca9ec419a51d"],
 " with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"], "=", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "478f2635-b019-42bb-8c5d-59e67685c8a2"],
 ", confirming the Poisson mean."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d1dcf1f7-b3fd-46f4-aed5-9ed146dc632f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Whether light is ",
 StyleBox["classical or nonclassical",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " is decided by photon statistics, not by mean intensity. The second-order \
coherence ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["g", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], "2", 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}]], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "0", 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"], 
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["a", "TI"]}], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "/", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"], 
      StyleBox["a", "TI"]}], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
     StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}], "2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1dfca560-7704-4c07-bf4c-29aa39be3a66"],
 " measures how photons bunch: a coherent (laser-like) field has ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["g", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], "2", 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}]], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "0", 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "82a89e3e-51a2-4d7d-8ebe-b0066c5772d3"],
 ", while a single-photon state has ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["g", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], "2", 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}]], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "0", 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", "0"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "89230f16-2689-4a0e-90fb-43ab717f3d98"],
 ", since one photon cannot be detected twice at once. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "G2Coherence"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "b9fcb2ec-9616-45af-abe9-9b5e122c5f7f"],
 " computes it from the state:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1801c2ea-670d-418d-b416-00b255c8519b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"G2Coherence", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"CoherentState", "[", "10", "]"}], "[", 
     RowBox[{"<|", 
      RowBox[{"\[FormalAlpha]", " ", "->", " ", "1.0"}], "|>"}], "]"}], "]"}],
    ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"G2Coherence", "[", 
    RowBox[{"FockState", "[", 
     RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "10"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[20]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"0581ef1a-617c-4d09-9efd-fcf0aeeb7023"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.9999918897646678`", ",", "0"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[20]= ",ExpressionUUID->"51353084-7f7a-4bde-9cc6-09907b2dd3d2"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The result is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1.0", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "643fab51-e795-4276-bfb7-42a715ef8374"],
 ": the coherent state sits exactly at the classical boundary, and the single \
photon is perfectly ",
 StyleBox["antibunched",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Any ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["g", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], "2", 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}]], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "0", 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "<", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a47cc945-b68d-47ce-96e5-4bef537b41b4"],
 " is impossible for classical light and is the experimental signature of a \
true quantum emitter."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f7398a14-e847-4602-acd4-c9eedce9c807"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The oscillator is also where the ",
 StyleBox["position-momentum uncertainty",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " lives. The quadratures ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], "=", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], "+", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "93854c3d-9a3f-4ced-b1e1-c7db0ac5474e"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["P", "TI"], "=", "-", 
   StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], "-", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "233d3459-c703-4249-8ceb-af548f77b36b"],
 " are the oscillator's \"position\" and \"momentum\"; in this normalization ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
    StyleBox["P", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   StyleBox["i", "TI"], "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4dbd85df-2f88-4246-b775-6b878019e9a5"],
 ". The ground state is a minimum-uncertainty state. Using the same ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "OperatorVariance"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "1162ae9e-05b9-4d36-88e0-6689d6ffd1ba"],
 " as in Part 2, verify that it saturates the bound:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"23448dae-747b-4f86-84c8-00126ca769a4"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"Xq", ",", " ", "Pq"}], "}"}], " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuadratureOperators", "[", "6", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"gs", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"FockState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", "6"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"OperatorVariance", "[", 
    RowBox[{"gs", ",", " ", "Xq"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"OperatorVariance", "[", 
    RowBox[{"gs", ",", " ", "Pq"}], "]"}], ",", "\n", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"OperatorVariance", "[", 
     RowBox[{"gs", ",", " ", "Xq"}], "]"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"OperatorVariance", "[", 
     RowBox[{"gs", ",", " ", "Pq"}], "]"}]}]}], "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[21]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"66e9b51b-610e-40f3-80e2-c22ca9633bee"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", "4"], ",", 
   FractionBox["1", "4"], ",", 
   FractionBox["1", "16"]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[21]= ",ExpressionUUID->"3d852985-7206-4560-a6d5-9e7f0a50eda7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This gives ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], "2"], "=", "\[CapitalDelta]", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P", "TI"], "2"], "=", "1", "/", "4"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0a2e5bf3-4259-49a8-927f-43b976669c8c"],
 " and a product ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "/", "16"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b6934966-b761-4377-b340-7ce36afb9ea7"],
 ", so ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], "\[CapitalDelta]", 
   StyleBox["P", "TI"], "=", "1", "/", "4", "=", 
   FractionBox["1", "2"], "\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   StyleBox["P", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "989f72fe-ee01-42b7-a780-cb0d5fccc454"],
 ". The vacuum is as sharp as quantum mechanics allows in both quadratures at \
once, the saturated case the strict qubit inequality of Part 2 anticipated."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6cf2c44f-5d09-4734-af3e-b122c44acfe3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Finally, the ",
 StyleBox["Jaynes-Cummings model",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " couples one qubit to one field mode, the elementary model of light-matter \
interaction in a cavity. On resonance and in the interaction picture, the \
coupling is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["H", "TI"], "=", 
   StyleBox["g", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], "+"], 
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], "+", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], "-"], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6f5c46bb-38e8-4ef3-9c3f-672ead576baf"],
 ", where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "75efbe45-6f91-48c3-944c-cf7763c7c83f"],
 " raise and lower the qubit and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["a", "TI"], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ee1e119a-e921-47a8-a869-0559724442dc"],
 " destroy and create photons. Build it on a qubit-times-field space and \
watch a single excitation oscillate between atom and cavity:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"dd9a49f8-a5f5-4d1a-8098-9dc690726847"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"nF", " ", "=", " ", "4"}], ";", " ", 
  RowBox[{"g", " ", "=", " ", "1"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Sigma]p", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"AnnihilationOperator", "[", "2", "]"}], "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", 
    "]"}]}], ";", " ", 
  RowBox[{"\[Sigma]m", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"AnnihilationOperator", "[", "2", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"af", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"AnnihilationOperator", "[", "nF", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Hjc", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"g", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"QuantumTensorProduct", "[", 
       RowBox[{"\[Sigma]p", ",", " ", "af"}], "]"}], " ", "+", " ", 
      RowBox[{"QuantumTensorProduct", "[", 
       RowBox[{"\[Sigma]m", ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"af", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ")"}]}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"psi0", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumTensorProduct", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<1\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"FockState", "[", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", "nF"}], "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"jc", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEvolve", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Hjc", ",", " ", "psi0", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"t", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "Pi"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"pe", "[", "tt_", "]"}], " ", ":=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"QuantumPartialTrace", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"jc", "[", 
         RowBox[{"<|", 
          RowBox[{"t", " ", "->", " ", "tt"}], "|>"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"{", "2", "}"}]}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<ProbabilitiesList\>\"", 
      "]"}], "[", 
     RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], " ", "//", " ", "Chop"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"pe", "[", "0", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"pe", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "4."}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"pe", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "2."}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[22]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"5e60dd21-3228-4e6a-ba88-263e71cf1319"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"1.`", ",", "0.5000000030916697`", ",", "0"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[22]= ",ExpressionUUID->"06691a4e-853d-4c04-bd04-a7726fc10baa"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The excited-state population is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1.", ",", " ", "0.5", ",", " ", "0."}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"09a22b63-5083-41b5-8759-9fb98a67e886"],
 ", matching ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["e", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["t", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["cos",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox[
    RowBox[{"g", "t"}], "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a47eb79a-d40b-459b-b797-90969e6be2f6"],
 ": the atom starts excited with the cavity empty (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    RowBox[{
      StyleBox["e", "TI"], ",\[ThinSpace]", "0"}]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2a299f76-8c48-4a6b-9dcf-13612e552423"],
 "), and the energy quantum coherently shuttles to the field (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    RowBox[{
      StyleBox["g", "TI"], ",\[ThinSpace]", "1"}]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "863d318c-11e6-4287-b363-3aeef06c740d"],
 ") and back. This ",
 StyleBox["vacuum Rabi oscillation",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " has no classical analog. The coupling term ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], "+"], 
   StyleBox["a", "TI"], "+", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], "-"], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2660c559-7f92-4425-ba64-8f75eb8c48a6"],
 " links ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    RowBox[{
      StyleBox["e", "TI"], ",\[ThinSpace]", "0"}]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "954120dc-28a7-4190-8d22-09d0b3b64345"],
 " directly to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    RowBox[{
      StyleBox["g", "TI"], ",\[ThinSpace]", "1"}]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "150bf909-6b6a-4847-80d3-e30c50581b98"],
 ", so even with zero photons in the cavity the initial state is not an \
eigenstate of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["H", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6be2d2ee-e804-4874-8cb7-1740ec5779e3"],
 " and is forced to evolve. A classical field of zero amplitude would leave \
the atom alone; the quantized field does not."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0e049a15-29d1-4934-ac60-193222613ab8"],

Cell["Part 6: Many qubits: tensor products, gates, circuits", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"05061bff-dbd8-4f29-b36a-92622dbb1611"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Two qubits live in the ",
 StyleBox["tensor product",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " of their spaces, a four-dimensional Hilbert space. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumTensorProduct"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "01eba25f-0fb8-4f03-81b2-bce79134d54e"],
 " builds composite states and operators:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d3fb6727-c3f0-45c9-bcfe-40616b8055e3"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"q00", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumTensorProduct", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<0\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<0\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"q00", "[", "\"\<Qudits\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"q00", "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
    "Normal"}]}], "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[23]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"f3299899-c13a-4641-b797-e17f10cac2cd"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"2", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"1", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[23]= ",ExpressionUUID->"f917c01b-1862-4fe6-8cfb-99374b42e939"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This reports ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "2"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"3b4edc43-4808-4ff7-9961-bc7cff33e301"],
 " qudits and the vector ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "1"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0", ",", "0"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8790ada0-7ae7-4395-a222-9eb3740f86bd"],
 ", that is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"00"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c9f6087c-254f-4d27-8eb6-dd304f1a9f1f"],
 ". The dimension doubles with every qubit added, which is precisely the \
resource that makes quantum computers powerful and classical simulation \
hard."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8ca4c167-8517-4924-93fb-3218d50573bf"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A ",
 StyleBox["quantum circuit",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " is an ordered list of gates acting on named wires. A gate is a unitary ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumOperator"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "40bf4622-5f56-4052-ab28-5011ea8a6af8"],
 "; the basic library includes the Hadamard ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<H\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "537175e9-8116-4c27-9dbc-3b17ffd5e634"],
 ", the Paulis, phase gates, and the controlled-NOT ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<CNOT\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a05c5f21-2125-4f7a-b08c-e726a23474d7"],
 ". Unitarity is what makes gates reversible, and we check it the \
object-model way:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5129719c-1c01-41af-b44b-44d760784829"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<H\>\"", "]"}], 
    "[", "\"\<UnitaryQ\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<CNOT\>\"", "]"}], 
    "[", "\"\<UnitaryQ\>\"", "]"}]}], "}"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[24]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"2d15892b-f44e-4a2d-aa8c-6765e22314c0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"True", ",", "True"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[24]= ",ExpressionUUID->"a87cdd69-195c-4ea6-a4f2-0c7e4f83ab9a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Both are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "True"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "ea0aebd6-a977-4010-b30d-edd72f427575"],
 ". The canonical two-qubit circuit prepares a Bell pair: a Hadamard on the \
first wire followed by a CNOT controlled on it:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d5d37e81-8cd2-4e8c-b02b-ed4d942e7a1d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"bell", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumCircuitOperator", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "1"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"bell", "[", 
    RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<00\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], 
   "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", "Normal"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[25]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"b85593cb-004c-455a-8226-20c0c1fafb32"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", 
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[25]= ",ExpressionUUID->"711821c3-e3ff-48f0-b0aa-43eecf912c29"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The output is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "1", "/", 
    SqrtBox["2"]}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0", ",", "0"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"1", "/", 
    SqrtBox["2"], "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1c786322-c87c-4851-97ad-3020d1197ca1"],
 ", the entangled state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["\[CapitalPhi]", "+"]},
    "Ket"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"00"},
       "Ket"], "+", 
      TemplateBox[{"11"},
       "Ket"]}], ")"}], "/", 
    SqrtBox["2"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "adb6cd9d-0b4b-4fb0-8a84-3ceb28174c42"],
 ". The notation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\"\<gate\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "wires"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"523f876b-8190-461f-aedb-fcf0b35b8bbf"],
 " reads like a wiring diagram, and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"bell", "[", "\"\<Diagram\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"503be315-00f5-434f-9376-4b1a92bed529"],
 " draws the actual circuit."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"71a416ae-3052-4a16-867b-6146c29cada6"],

Cell["\<\
Circuits compose and scale. The three-qubit GHZ state, a maximally entangled \
\"cat\" state, is one more CNOT:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"75a598fa-7e62-4c11-a690-2d79a13f43d1"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<GHZ\>\"", "[", "3", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"",
    "]"}], " ", "//", " ", "Normal"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[26]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"28e938c2-37a8-4f95-8eaf-81dc37d3972e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0",
    ",", 
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[26]= ",ExpressionUUID->"6d515ec2-969b-4df9-8e90-4fc2fd771aa8"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "which is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "1", "/", 
    SqrtBox["2"]}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"1", "/", 
    SqrtBox["2"], "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a8436d4e-a944-42e6-ad55-8b59b58684d7"],
 ", the state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"000"},
      "Ket"], "+", 
     TemplateBox[{"111"},
      "Ket"]}], ")"}], "/", 
   SqrtBox["2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "45e7baa8-1fde-411e-aa17-674046ab67f3"],
 ". Gates and circuits are the hardware-independent logical layer of quantum \
computing: the same ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "bell"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "23dd9476-2d4b-458b-aaeb-ad1d12e3fe67"],
 " circuit runs on any platform."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bb019aa9-be9c-489d-864d-9cb563157e3f"],

Cell["\<\
Part 7: Communication: entanglement, no-cloning, teleportation\
\>", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"bef56052-3cb9-4e25-a903-3888139a97d3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Quantum communication rests on ",
 StyleBox["entanglement",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", correlation stronger than anything classical. The Bell state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["\[CapitalPhi]", "+"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2914f4fb-9262-4039-92c9-be9f10348c07"],
 " is entangled, and the framework can certify it:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"235ffde8-7c0f-422f-9c4b-77dae298693c"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"bell", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<PhiPlus\>\"", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QuantumEntangledQ", "[", "bell", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEntanglementMonotone", "[", 
    RowBox[{"bell", ",", " ", "\"\<Concurrence\>\""}], "]"}]}], 
  "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[27]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"c5780477-f64a-4b55-ab0a-5e91df02a2e3"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"True", ",", "1"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[27]= ",ExpressionUUID->"c01d78e3-18b0-4b5f-8d88-63a6c2f9bdd8"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "returns ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"True", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "534cf91e-a2be-4159-ab2c-3a30c94bfb88"],
 ": not only is the state entangled, its concurrence is the maximum value ",
 Cell[BoxData["1"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "dad467a6-0cc8-44b3-9194-37ca0643d76b"],
 ". The signature of entanglement is that the ",
 StyleBox["parts",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " are less defined than the whole. Trace out the second qubit and inspect \
what is left of the first:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"04f884a4-cda6-4c8e-b957-057418d429fe"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"QuantumPartialTrace", "[", 
   RowBox[{"bell", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", "2", "}"}]}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<Purity\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[28]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"0fcb981b-3144-481c-ab74-bde08a4a426d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox["1", "2"]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[28]= ",ExpressionUUID->"5498d76d-af46-4991-bd04-36f0603098c7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The reduced state has purity ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c17deabc-b730-406d-9ecd-08fea0931668"],
 ", the minimum possible for a qubit: it is ",
 StyleBox["maximally mixed",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". The whole is a perfectly definite pure state, yet each half, looked at \
alone, is maximally random. That trade-off is the engine of both \
teleportation and quantum cryptography."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5785e8dd-aff5-4c0b-a25c-09e0531ed8a4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A second pillar is the ",
 StyleBox["no-cloning theorem",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": no operation can copy an unknown quantum state. We can see why with the \
CNOT gate, which ",
 StyleBox["does", "TI"],
 " copy the basis states (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"]}], "\[Rule]", 
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3e050141-718d-4a92-bba7-216e2dd82557"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"]}], "\[Rule]", 
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a10bdf4f-e81b-4bae-8556-44e354754c48"],
 "). Try to use it to copy a superposition:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"047a9fb2-1405-43ef-b0cf-23919aabe935"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"cnot", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumCircuitOperator", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"copied", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"cnot", "[", 
    RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+0\>\"", "]"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"target", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumTensorProduct", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Abs", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"copied", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", 
      "target"}], ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], "^", 
  "2"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[29]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"5d6348cb-6609-458f-bd69-d529ef111b54"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox["1", "2"]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[29]= ",ExpressionUUID->"67e0def0-06a6-43f5-8869-1e8bf10b006f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The fidelity between what CNOT produces and a genuine copy ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{"+"},
    "Ket"], 
   TemplateBox[{"+"},
    "Ket"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0f5f6113-82e3-4630-9b48-5cd823c9438d"],
 " is only ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "335d3b80-de25-44c7-a11d-c7fc27dcec06"],
 ". Instead of two copies of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"+"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4615bc8d-0cc8-4f90-bc40-699609381961"],
 ", CNOT produces the entangled Bell state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"00"},
      "Ket"], "+", 
     TemplateBox[{"11"},
      "Ket"]}], ")"}], "/", 
   SqrtBox["2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "70b860c4-353f-41ff-8121-5ed8b5f1a611"],
 ". A machine that copies a basis cannot copy its superpositions; that is \
no-cloning, made concrete."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5ea0f05c-71bb-4fc7-8efb-77e1362e712e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "No-cloning forbids copying, but ",
 StyleBox["teleportation",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " still lets Alice send an unknown qubit to Bob using a shared Bell pair and \
two classical bits, destroying her original in the process. The protocol: \
entangle a helper pair (wires 2 and 3), have Alice interact her unknown qubit \
(wire 1) with her half, measure wires 1 and 2, and have Bob apply a \
correction to wire 3 conditioned on the two outcomes. Build it and run an \
unknown state through:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d4966418-4e8c-4470-804d-2c62dd4db06e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"psiIn", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"N", " ", "@", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
        RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "5"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Exp", "[", 
         RowBox[{"I", " ", 
          RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "3"}]}], "]"}], " ", 
        RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
         RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "5"}], "]"}]}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"tele", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumCircuitOperator", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "2"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"2", ",", " ", "3"}], "}"}]}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "1"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"meas", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"tele", "[", 
    RowBox[{"QuantumTensorProduct", "[", 
     RowBox[{"psiIn", ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<00\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Values", "[", 
   RowBox[{"meas", "[", "\"\<Probabilities\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], " ", "//", " ",
   "N"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[30]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"2cfd86d3-5d49-440b-ae08-9213e5e109de"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.25`", ",", "0.25`", ",", "0.25`", ",", "0.25`"}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[30]= ",ExpressionUUID->"31096ca0-fbbf-4241-9917-671bbfd1857b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The four measurement outcomes are equally likely, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0.25"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], "0.25", 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], "0.25", 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0.25", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e5275ace-d93f-428c-9a1b-ad28e5114816"],
 ", so the measurement leaks ",
 StyleBox["nothing",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " about the state. The post-measurement states on Bob's wire are the \
conditional outputs ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"meas", "[", "\"\<States\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"94d4d2db-8d89-4540-ba2a-fb0a2ea5dae7"],
 ". For each outcome ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["m", "TI"], "1"], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["m", "TI"], "2"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5778574c-d25e-4e50-8402-08b6473e97ab"],
 ", Bob's correction is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["m", "TI"], "1"]], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["m", "TI"], "2"]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7cc99421-8f56-452c-b09e-af5cdd920795"],
 ". Apply it and verify perfect recovery:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"47b58b09-bbf2-4882-ae8b-04ddeda31f51"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"corr", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"<|", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}], " ", "->", " ", "\"\<I\>\""}], ",",
      " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], " ", "->", " ", "\"\<X\>\""}], ",",
      " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}], " ", "->", " ", "\"\<Z\>\""}], ",",
      " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], " ", "->", " ", "\"\<Y\>\""}]}], 
    "|>"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"KeyValueMap", "[", "\n", "  ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Function", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"k", ",", " ", "st"}], "}"}], ",", "\n", "    ", 
     RowBox[{"Module", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"outcome", " ", "=", " ", 
          RowBox[{"First", "[", "k", "]"}]}], ",", " ", "q3"}], "}"}], ",", 
       "\n", "      ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"q3", " ", "=", " ", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"QuantumPartialTrace", "[", 
           RowBox[{"st", ",", " ", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
             RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], 
          "[", "\"\<Normalize\>\"", "]"}]}], ";", "\n", "      ", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"outcome", ",", " ", 
          RowBox[{"Round", "[", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"Abs", "[", 
              RowBox[{
               RowBox[{"(", 
                RowBox[{
                 RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"(", 
                   RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"corr", "[", "outcome", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "q3", 
                    "]"}], "[", "\"\<Normalize\>\"", "]"}], ")"}], 
                  "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", "psiIn"}], 
                ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], "^", "2"}], ",", 
            " ", "0.001"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}]}], "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", "\n", 
   "  ", 
   RowBox[{"meas", "[", "\"\<StateAssociation\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], "Input",\

 CellLabel->
  "In[31]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"d50f83a8-c35f-4889-935c-ef25f1f9608a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", "0"}], "}"}], ",", "1.`"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], "}"}], ",", "1.`"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"1", ",", "0"}], "}"}], ",", "1.`"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"1", ",", "1"}], "}"}], ",", "1.`"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",\

 CellLabel->
  "Out[31]= ",ExpressionUUID->"0f4386bc-a26d-457f-b387-0b63f6c78a57"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Every branch returns fidelity ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "1."], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "5495505d-8416-4d61-bdaf-e3f3c651ce80"],
 ": regardless of which of the four random outcomes occurred, Bob's corrected \
qubit is ",
 StyleBox["exactly",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " the state Alice sent. The state crossed the channel carried by one Bell \
pair and two classical bits, with no copy left behind and no information in \
the transmitted bits alone."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a6ead3c2-8271-460a-b280-09e1edf44c93"],

Cell["\<\
Part 8: Open systems: mixed states, channels, and decoherence\
\>", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"f0dc56be-3848-4ab4-b20a-b5043426cf70"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Every real device is open to its environment, and an open system is \
generally not in a pure state. The complete description is the ",
 StyleBox["density operator",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b7d5d4a7-6702-48ef-b193-cc686ba63a91"],
 ", a positive operator of unit trace. A classical mixture of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "82ce76c5-12d0-4eb7-beb5-9d030fdf1833"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f235b9be-4d14-47aa-ba3a-c76a7019811a"],
 " is diagonal:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e301b9b5-9ad7-452f-b1e7-3cd558a4d72c"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"rho", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"0.75", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", "0.25"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"rho", "[", "\"\<PureStateQ\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"rho", "[", "\"\<Purity\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"rho", "[", "\"\<VonNeumannEntropy\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"rho", "[", "\"\<BlochVector\>\"", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[32]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"a23d53b9-3860-4a27-9b14-4ddfc14e8a0b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"False", ",", "0.625`", ",", 
   TemplateBox[{"0.8112781244591328`", "\"b\"", "bits", "\"Bits\""},
    "Quantity"], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", "0.5`"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[32]= ",ExpressionUUID->"752cbe2d-9a27-4d51-8e9f-ce5761b484ce"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This reports ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "False"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "f78e7b9b-2a12-4b78-b017-4e7db6605469"],
 " (not pure), purity ",
 Cell[BoxData["0.625"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "aea88153-7ce2-4354-aefe-f7cf69a31b3b"],
 ", von Neumann entropy ",
 Cell[BoxData["0.811"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f2ddda17-5614-44cd-854c-ddb60855f969"],
 " bits, and Bloch vector ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], "0", 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0.5", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ccafcded-cb45-4c0f-9afa-e91180d862d4"],
 ". Purity ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["Tr",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], " ", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], "2"], "<", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f0ae302b-830c-4bc9-ae4b-381afe1af4bf"],
 " and nonzero entropy are the marks of a mixed state, and its Bloch vector \
lies strictly ",
 StyleBox["inside",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " the sphere. The maximally mixed state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["I", "TI"], "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6d36b3f0-2ee7-46c4-b55a-14d6fc50cc90"],
 " sits at the origin with purity ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "602e0aa2-aaff-4082-b818-8daa25e66f10"],
 " and one full bit of entropy."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a4420170-4bcc-4dd8-948d-5e46fd5f67de"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Decoherence is mixing caused by entanglement with an environment. We \
already saw it in Part 7: the reduced state of a Bell pair is maximally \
mixed. The general lesson is that ",
 StyleBox["tracing out",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " an inaccessible partner turns pure into mixed. That is decoherence in one \
move."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7483878c-e831-445d-a47f-4827fff09374"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For Markovian environments, the dynamics of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "12e6d0d2-c8aa-4eee-939e-26c5015e16b1"],
 " obey the ",
 StyleBox["Lindblad master equation",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumEvolve"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "28f0f381-de78-4ba0-939b-63d39d3e3147"],
 " integrates it when you supply collapse (jump) operators as a rule ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "L", "}"}], " ", "->", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", "rate", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a4727237-4981-4439-8296-9ab9cc3c63e6"],
 " together with an initial density matrix. The two canonical processes are \
energy decay (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], "1"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "48208d4f-777e-48d8-a751-0e8738d37f15"],
 ") and dephasing (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "272af83a-47fc-4deb-a329-8c014b8c40e1"],
 ")."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"89da6609-b1eb-47c5-b2c0-b5f03ba53c34"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Energy relaxation: the excited state decays to the ground state. The jump \
operator is the qubit lowering operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], "-"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Bra"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f1fe2902-6c51-4ae0-b72b-3adc3c152bc8"],
 ", which is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"AnnihilationOperator", "[", "2", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"1700ca4f-628a-4e06-87b7-0347f275b1cf"],
 ". With no coherent drive the Hamiltonian is zero, written natively as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"0", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<I\>\"", "]"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"16682002-5147-44cf-a8d3-088ffb209cc1"],
 ". Evolve ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a467a3e9-54c2-4643-a707-5d0dcd74d753"],
 " at rate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Gamma]", "TI"], "=", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "36bf04b7-2b0d-4581-8fb7-737c4129016b"],
 " and read the excited population:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"651d9c03-4c89-4b92-8091-622ec6b81aea"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Hzero", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"0", " ", 
    RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<I\>\"", "]"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"sm", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"AnnihilationOperator", "[", "2", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"t1", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEvolve", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Hzero", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", "sm", "}"}], " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}]}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<1\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"t", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "3"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"p1", "[", "tt_", "]"}], " ", ":=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"t1", "[", 
       RowBox[{"<|", 
        RowBox[{"t", " ", "->", " ", "tt"}], "|>"}], "]"}], 
      "[", "\"\<ProbabilitiesList\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
     RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], " ", "//", " ", "Chop"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"p1", "[", "0", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"p1", "[", "1.", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"p1", "[", "2.", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[33]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"f3d3ee19-3140-43c9-a18a-4b2f93c736d1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"1.`", ",", "0.3678766862006472`", ",", "0.13533458165972925`"}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[33]= ",ExpressionUUID->"6ad26581-5d3b-4ace-84aa-e7cbe3947932"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The populations ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1.", ",", " ", "0.368", ",", " ", "0.135"}], "}"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"627eed4b-83ae-4f52-aea0-234cb8fc6405"],
 " trace out ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P", "TI"], "1"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["t", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{"-", 
     StyleBox["\[Gamma]", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["t", "TI"]}]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "70e6a12d-7c50-4c50-b645-1e13ce9de18c"],
 " exactly: exponential decay with lifetime ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T", "TI"], "1"], "=", "1", "/", 
   StyleBox["\[Gamma]", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f8bdeca4-96f8-4d7d-8959-2bc5c5e7d56d"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4f8392a6-1584-4a02-8824-f2b2510a5771"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Dephasing: the populations survive but the ",
 StyleBox["coherence",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " between ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f1e425dc-8e32-412c-9224-67b3bfa1613e"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c0a18acc-c365-405b-845e-fbaedab57140"],
 " decays, randomizing the phase. The jump operator is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9ea19bfb-b73b-435f-8a5a-155c5ce8aa80"],
 ". Evolve ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"+"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bd098613-1e9a-4d27-b510-1df0353f2156"],
 " and watch the Bloch vector's transverse component collapse:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"13bfdb2a-d698-4106-9519-ace6979dee11"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"t2", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEvolve", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Hzero", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Z\>\"", "]"}], "}"}], " ", "->", 
      " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}]}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"t", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"bx", "[", "tt_", "]"}], " ", ":=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"t2", "[", 
       RowBox[{"<|", 
        RowBox[{"t", " ", "->", " ", "tt"}], "|>"}], "]"}], 
      "[", "\"\<BlochVector\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
     RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], " ", "//", " ", "Chop"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"bx", "[", "0", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"bx", "[", "0.5", "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"bx", "[", "1.", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[34]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"9e222d41-c542-4008-815b-433057f1fdbd"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"1.`", ",", "0.36787858729627604`", ",", "0.13533435961982623`"}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[34]= ",ExpressionUUID->"83e5f856-c9ae-4f68-811a-37dac3239ea3"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The transverse Bloch component ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1.", ",", " ", "0.368", ",", " ", "0.135"}], "}"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"ea9a772a-19e2-4acb-b538-7a5fe6eec4f3"],
 " decays as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
   RowBox[{"-", "2", 
    StyleBox["\[Gamma]", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["t", "TI"]}]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2b9ced27-9043-4094-bae7-cdbefb320a2d"],
 " while the populations (the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0b43bc9e-e7f7-4239-83d6-16d835bdabaa"],
 "-component) stay put. On the Bloch sphere the arrow spirals inward toward \
the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3ff45fa7-1bc7-4957-9ba8-88c183ac0337"],
 "-axis: the state is losing the phase coherence that lets it interfere, \
while its energy populations survive intact. That picture makes decoherence \
physical, and it is exactly the process the sensor of Part 9 must outrun."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ebef659e-cc08-4487-833c-6eeb1b4b5007"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "It is often cleaner to think of a noise process as a ",
 StyleBox["channel",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", a map that sends states to states in one shot, summarizing the \
environment without time-resolving it. The framework's ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumChannel"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "1d3b2263-e8b7-4a2f-97d9-9ebb078a6f31"],
 " carries the standard qubit noise models. Each one moves the Bloch vector \
in a characteristic way:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a4393c8a-40d4-460e-8ed1-b064c49d2109"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"{", "\n", "  ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"QuantumChannel", "[", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<BitFlip\>\"", "[", "0.1", "]"}], "]"}], "[", 
      RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<0\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], 
     "[", "\"\<ProbabilitiesList\>\"", "]"}], ",", "\n", "  ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"QuantumChannel", "[", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<AmplitudeDamping\>\"", "[", "0.3", "]"}], "]"}], "[", 
      RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<1\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], 
     "[", "\"\<ProbabilitiesList\>\"", "]"}], ",", "\n", "  ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"QuantumChannel", "[", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<Depolarizing\>\"", "[", "0.4", "]"}], "]"}], "[", 
      RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], 
     "[", "\"\<BlochVector\>\"", "]"}], ",", "\n", "  ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"QuantumChannel", "[", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<PhaseDamping\>\"", "[", "0.5", "]"}], "]"}], "[", 
      RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], 
     "[", "\"\<BlochVector\>\"", "]"}]}], "\n", "}"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "Chop"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[35]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"36d75a5d-43c0-449b-90c3-9a7816005f9c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0.9`", ",", "0.10000000000000002`"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0.29999999999999993`", ",", "0.7000000000000001`"}], "}"}], ",", 
   
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0.6`", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0.7071067811865475`", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "}"}]}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[35]= ",ExpressionUUID->"ef98e5e1-b447-46c4-b032-9a9947bfdc8f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Reading the four results: a bit-flip with probability ",
 Cell[BoxData["0.1"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d5842234-6525-46a9-a8bf-22a8f4c13e9a"],
 " leaves ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "71372458-29c6-47c9-8b2d-cb5fc7f0f604"],
 " as the mixture ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0.9"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0.1", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fa5132c0-8568-4cb4-98b6-0b3d1530f77f"],
 "; amplitude damping with strength ",
 Cell[BoxData["0.3"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e2537c73-b6e1-438d-8609-2f0d354c00d8"],
 " partially relaxes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "de819c38-561c-40c1-b1f5-a2c21fe513ca"],
 " toward the ground state, giving populations ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0.3"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"0.7", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8fd23cfb-1e64-4511-bed7-651cbb47011b"],
 "; depolarizing shrinks the Bloch vector of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"+"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b6528404-85f7-4ed3-a8c7-db6ffebde9af"],
 " by the factor ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "-", 
   StyleBox["p", "TI"], "=", "0.6"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "75142188-964c-45c9-a289-cc49007a4251"],
 ", toward the maximally mixed center; and phase damping multiplies the \
transverse coherence by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{"1", "-", 
     StyleBox["\[Lambda]", "TI"]}]], "=", 
   SqrtBox["0.5"], "\[TildeTilde]", "0.707"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "013cdf66-6546-4d81-a89b-06b3f585cfe4"],
 " while leaving populations untouched. The channel picture and the Lindblad \
picture are two views of the same decoherence; the channel is what you apply \
once per gate, the master equation is what you integrate over continuous time."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d4cc2eeb-21ad-48e2-bed9-30227a8cb22e"],

Cell["Part 9: Quantum sensing", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"89d4a861-3332-4d21-9377-d262cb50b463"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Quantum sensing turns the fragility of Part 8 into an asset. A qubit whose \
energy splitting depends on an external field is a field meter: let it \
accumulate phase, and read the field off the phase. The standard protocol is ",
 StyleBox["Ramsey interferometry",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". A ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c6967ff3-fe70-4dea-bd40-b553e8f9605e"],
 "-pulse puts the qubit on the equator, the qubit then precesses for a time \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e33c238c-2b67-40cf-bc7f-c0b8ab87a98e"],
 " and accumulates a phase ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Phi]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ae36fe81-bd61-45a8-8f30-29facad1e9af"],
 " proportional to the field, and a second ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8ae6fff0-c386-4f9e-931b-ac4c6399c20d"],
 "-pulse converts that phase into a population we can measure."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d42eb42f-c3bf-4645-8066-178ee3fbb08b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Model the sequence with two Hadamards bracketing a phase gate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["P", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["\[Phi]", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   StyleBox["diag",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"1", 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
     StyleBox[
      RowBox[{"i", "\[Phi]"}], "TI"]]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4cc56af1-4a85-4f26-9ab9-98d28374eb1f"],
 ", and read the ground-state probability:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"70056f15-0fbd-403e-ab38-d421b826c13b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"ramsey", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumCircuitOperator", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "1"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<P\>\"", "[", "\[Phi]", "]"}], " ", "->", " ", "1"}], ",", 
      " ", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"out", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"ramsey", "[", 
    RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<0\>\"", "]"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"P0", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"out", "[", "\"\<ProbabilitiesList\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
     RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Assumptions", " ", "->", " ", 
     RowBox[{"\[Phi]", " ", "\[Element]", " ", "Reals"}]}]}], 
   "]"}]}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[36]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"05b10102-6fbd-47d4-849a-e5dc7c268bf4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 SuperscriptBox[
  RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
   FractionBox["\[Phi]", "2"], "]"}], "2"]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[36]= ",ExpressionUUID->"186cdc5a-3181-4d3d-a1e2-5707c67f31ec"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The framework returns ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P", "TI"], "0"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["\[Phi]", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["cos",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Phi]", "TI"], "/", "2"}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ad96e12a-f535-4547-a64b-fa0a4e111d7e"],
 ": a textbook ",
 StyleBox["Ramsey fringe",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Since the accumulated phase is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Phi]", "TI"], "=", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Gamma]", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["q", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["B", "TI"], " ", 
   StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "406eb4c1-ddae-4335-81de-c22c09df4952"],
 " for a magnetic field ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["B", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "75c48a45-44fd-4438-be05-2cf4971d7eca"],
 " (with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["\[Gamma]", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["q", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "447674dc-c422-4697-99a9-f7f83d8d763c"],
 " the qubit's gyromagnetic ratio), the measured probability oscillates with \
the field. Counting fringes measures ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["B", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7f9d0784-2c94-45fb-b99a-8cd0de1d2fbe"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c5bb2467-fe97-4d7b-8454-52c2b982c376"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The precision is set by how steeply the signal responds to the phase. \
Compute the sensitivity ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["P", "TI"], "0"], "/", "\[PartialD]", 
   StyleBox["\[Phi]", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e4b4c636-ee13-4f92-8046-6a8fd113eb52"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"de5e8475-9695-496f-88d6-38f438c7c414"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"D", "[", 
   RowBox[{"P0", ",", " ", "\[Phi]"}], "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "FullSimplify"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[37]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"0f001eb3-df83-4d2f-b4f6-2a8cc0a58eff"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"-", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "\[Phi]", "]"}], "2"]}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[37]= ",ExpressionUUID->"29cb5ba2-d6ea-4d54-83da-8b65dd6bb02b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"-", 
   FractionBox["1", "2"], 
   StyleBox["sin",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["\[Phi]", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9811b188-6431-48e9-b6bf-e6ff4d43c77f"],
 ", which is largest in magnitude at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Phi]", "TI"], "=", "\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9015016c-ca59-4613-ba4b-d8e431cd4384"],
 ". A well-designed magnetometer biases the interferometer to that steepest \
point, where a tiny change in field produces the largest change in signal."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c3c7c72c-f6c0-489b-90b8-1fb44caaab70"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Decoherence is what ultimately limits the sensitivity, which is why a \
realistic magnetometer must be analyzed together with its noise. During the \
free-evolution time ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "cd773eb7-3f68-4e2c-acab-259765f9dc7d"],
 ", dephasing erodes the fringe ",
 StyleBox["contrast",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Add a dephasing jump operator during the precession and track the \
transverse Bloch length, which is the contrast:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"77ff4a8f-4e66-4635-870e-345d0eb9f93e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"free", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumEvolve", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], ")"}], " ", 
      RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Z\>\"", "]"}]}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Z\>\"", "]"}], "}"}], " ", "->", 
      " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", "0.3", "}"}]}], ",", "\n", "   ", 
     RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", "\"\<+\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"t", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "6"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"tt", ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"Norm", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"free", "[", 
          RowBox[{"<|", 
           RowBox[{"t", " ", "->", " ", "tt"}], "|>"}], "]"}], 
         "[", "\"\<BlochVector\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
        RowBox[{"[", 
         RowBox[{"1", " ", ";;", " ", "2"}], "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], ",",
     " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"tt", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "6", ",", " ", "1.5"}], "}"}]}], 
   "]"}], " ", "//", " ", "Chop"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[38]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"632a01c5-6336-40e6-8ef1-8f3fb24ae054"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "1.`"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"1.5`", ",", "0.40656992040570766`"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"3.`", ",", "0.1653002161976581`"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"4.5`", ",", "0.0672068827664922`"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"6.`", ",", "0.027323708691246146`"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[38]= ",ExpressionUUID->"40a3c88b-e0bb-4e09-b60a-f6096f2518f5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The contrast falls off as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
   RowBox[{"-", "2", 
    StyleBox["\[Gamma]", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"]}]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0e8c3b4f-98b2-4e8d-85a3-78d72c49a902"],
 ", from ",
 Cell[BoxData["1"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "68da34ac-7f54-414c-9d33-90072d728a13"],
 " at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"], "=", "0"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4c03aa1b-aad7-4e28-9ec7-589257a3072a"],
 " to about ",
 Cell[BoxData["0.027"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5d32d3d6-4d1b-4716-9a80-eb901d856ad4"],
 " by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"], "=", "6"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "259d03d3-20b0-4fbc-bd0d-61d9b5530768"],
 ". There is a sweet spot: you want the longest interrogation time ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7666cc15-d29c-4159-841d-c5a9104a9328"],
 " to accumulate the most phase, but only up to the coherence time ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bf85733a-972e-4126-ac9b-67bb2129faa7"],
 ", beyond which the fringe washes out and information stops accumulating. \
The optimal ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"], "\[Tilde]", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T", "TI"], "2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "123761db-81de-42e6-bb74-53c8efeb1b4b"],
 " is the central design trade-off in quantum sensing, and it is the same ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "30761a5c-427f-4bdb-8539-c5a7a2e96454"],
 " we computed in Part 8. A nitrogen-vacancy center in diamond is one \
physical realization of exactly this qubit-magnetometer, with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "44929386-0de9-451a-8578-929888c51b77"],
 " set by the surrounding nuclear spin bath."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"96dce3e0-4703-4f4b-aad1-0436eb86bfa4"],

Cell["Where this leaves us", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6091f3ef-bf9b-4e96-bd3f-0e2a51a9ad09"],

Cell["\<\
We have rebuilt the spine of quantum systems engineering as a sequence of \
computations. Along the way we constructed a reusable toolkit, all of it in \
one framework:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c0a8d79f-51e2-4c27-9b17-35b00d2fb27b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["The object model.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Every quantity came from asking an object a question: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"[", "\"\<HermitianQ\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "030dfac6-6d65-4d62-b851-e1e7113bb7e0"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"[", "\"\<UnitaryQ\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "697be622-5f59-46c6-b66b-1f04291f2ba2"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"[", "\"\<BlochVector\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "e84a58d4-417b-460a-a47c-27ab55ab6265"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"[", "\"\<Purity\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "d784d049-4232-46d3-b56c-4ea1565bf95a"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"[", "\"\<PureStateQ\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a2afd63e-24e6-400c-9da8-2742586f2856"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"[", "\"\<ProbabilitiesList\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"da4af32c-fe0e-493c-b2a8-108c152175a7"],
 ", plus ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "OperatorVariance"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a318490a-b2c8-4a0c-8458-1232c1c1397b"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Commutator"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "64ca89b6-ff83-4204-b135-b33c6299f0b8"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "G2Coherence"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "27f6ef8a-3b36-4d5f-beca-e11f03332fd1"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumEntanglementMonotone"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a283d4bd-7f11-4f43-b11c-45658be3f2c2"],
 ". We built matrices only to ",
 StyleBox["create", "TI"],
 " operators, never to interrogate them."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"90cf67f6-8f57-4386-94d4-9b8d198dd55c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["States and observables.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumState"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "07997e8d-a972-4857-ba2b-12fa5088863a"],
 " for kets and density matrices; ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumOperator"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "816ef85f-6328-40cc-801f-425f830ef1ae"],
 " for observables, Hamiltonians, and gates; expectation values and overlaps \
from ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"bra", "[", "\"\<Dagger\>\"", "]"}], " ", "@", " ", "ket"}], 
    ")"}], "[", "\"\<Scalar\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "fd46d606-f238-47a6-ac71-759755dd2c2f"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"1a7d38f5-1f34-4c54-896d-2e6a9bf78f9c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Dynamics.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumEvolve"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "da46337b-d0c7-42b0-9849-00d8c8da020a"],
 " for closed-form unitary evolution (no time range), numerically integrated \
trajectories (with a range), the Heisenberg picture (pass an observable), and \
Lindblad master equations (pass jump operators), in any picture."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"37e02332-78e5-41cc-9a34-8adb6b9da297"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["The two model systems.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " The driven qubit with its resonant and detuned Rabi flopping, on the Bloch \
sphere; the harmonic oscillator with ladder operators, Fock and coherent \
states, the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["g", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], "2", 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}]], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "0", 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "180c4eb1-3314-4ec4-9e1b-2af09d52702b"],
 " test for nonclassical light, quadrature uncertainty, and Jaynes-Cummings \
light-matter coupling."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3a6ed188-bb3d-454d-b2e2-0af198252d46"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Computing and communication.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Tensor products, gate circuits, Bell and GHZ entanglement, the no-cloning \
obstruction, and teleportation verified at unit fidelity."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d8ea21e9-db07-47f3-9f07-5443946287e9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Open systems and sensing.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Mixed states and entropy; the Lindblad master equation for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], "1"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4c7bf3f1-5bdc-4724-a4f4-42e2a21c087d"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5ab75920-cb50-4c94-9e30-2cb1a0b09921"],
 "; the standard noise channels; and Ramsey magnetometry whose precision is \
bounded by the very decoherence we modeled."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a1dd993c-e1e6-4b77-8b01-2992cbb2ced1"],

Cell["\<\
The reward is hardware-independent intuition: nothing above committed to a \
platform, yet everything is a faithful, runnable model of what \
superconducting qubits, trapped ions, photonic modes, and NV centers actually \
do. To go further, swap in real device parameters, push the circuits to more \
qubits, replace the idealized channels with measured noise spectra, or send a \
circuit to real hardware. The framework that drew the Bloch sphere will also \
talk to a quantum processor.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"095792f7-6797-4a1d-b492-cedfd28d2908"],

Cell["Four extended examples", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b7a5ef27-f404-424f-81e2-857212ae7e58"],

Cell["\<\
These four examples weave several threads from above into self-contained \
computations you can run and modify. Each draws on the parts it extends but \
stands on its own.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c69793f4-bc55-47cc-81d5-d87d30390a48"],

